{
  "texts": [
    "The cited references provide easy access for end users to perform fact-checking on the model generations.",
    "Most existing work (Malaviya et al., 2023; Sun et al., 2023; Li et al., 2023b; Kamalloo et al., 2023) simply prompts LLMs (e.g., ChatGPT) to include citations in their generation.",
    "Gao et al. (2023b) conduct systematic evaluations to show that the model performance can often be far from satisfactory with such prompting approaches.",
    "In this paper, we aim to study how we can train an LM to perform better at attributable generation.One challenge in achieving this goal comes from the expensive cost of collecting supervised training data that contains gold generations interleaved with citations.",
    "Another challenge stems from the finegrained task objective."
  ]
}